<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 05 at 7:26PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Gilmer
and north central Pickens Counties through 800 PM EDT...
At 726 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Talona, or 7 miles
north of Jasper, moving north at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Ellijay, East Ellijay, Talona, Tails Creek and Cartecay.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
